1
00:01:32,140 --> 00:01:34,497
Big truck's
comin' up through here.

2
00:01:34,817 --> 00:01:37,734
Ah, it'd be a mess
of potholes come spring.

3
00:01:38,014 --> 00:01:40,451
Yeah.

4
00:01:42,330 --> 00:01:45,245
Is someone new
moving into town?

5
00:01:45,565 --> 00:01:48,001
Haven't heard anything yet.

6
00:01:59,191 --> 00:02:01,228
I just want more hay.

7
00:02:01,509 --> 00:02:02,866
You what?

8
00:02:03,187 --> 00:02:04,504
I want more hay.

9
00:02:04,785 --> 00:02:05,703
Oh, who's this?

10
00:02:06,024 --> 00:02:08,939
Look at this.

11
00:02:09,219 --> 00:02:10,338
Whoa!

12
00:02:10,618 --> 00:02:12,215
Well, well, well, if it isn't
the Reed brothers.

13
00:02:12,496 --> 00:02:13,455
I've been lookin' for you boys.

14
00:02:13,776 --> 00:02:15,093
Do my eyes deceive me?

15
00:02:15,374 --> 00:02:17,290
You know, I heard
you were mayor,

16
00:02:17,611 --> 00:02:18,888
but it turns out
you're the handyman.

17
00:02:19,169 --> 00:02:21,566
Funny, you can't trust
a rumor mill, can you?

18
00:02:21,847 --> 00:02:24,243
Mitch Bright.

19
00:02:24,564 --> 00:02:27,760
Well, when you're
the mayor of a small town,

20
00:02:28,041 --> 00:02:30,755
you got to wear
a lot of different hats.

21
00:02:32,355 --> 00:02:33,712
You buildin' a new edition?

22
00:02:33,993 --> 00:02:35,550
You're funny.

23
00:02:35,831 --> 00:02:38,867
We're buildin' a platform
for the town Christmas display.

24
00:02:39,188 --> 00:02:41,545
You might remember it, huh?

25
00:02:41,825 --> 00:02:44,222
I don't know, we just
figured after five decades,

26
00:02:44,503 --> 00:02:47,618
the mother of God deserved
a proper place to kneel.

27
00:02:47,939 --> 00:02:48,777
It's only right.

28
00:02:49,098 --> 00:02:50,615
All the statues
and everything?
Yeah, right.

29
00:02:50,936 --> 00:02:52,094
I remember that.

30
00:02:52,373 --> 00:02:53,611
So how you guys doin'?

31
00:02:53,932 --> 00:02:55,529
Good.
Wow.

32
00:02:55,850 --> 00:02:57,447
How long has it been?

33
00:02:57,768 --> 00:02:59,684
I'm thinkin'

34
00:03:00,845 --> 00:03:02,762
What brings you
to town, Mitch?
some hotshot attorney--

35
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:06,477
Oh, he's loaded now.

36
00:03:06,758 --> 00:03:07,637
Who struck it rich.

37
00:03:07,917 --> 00:03:09,674
Yeah, I've made some
good investments, you know,

38
00:03:09,955 --> 00:03:11,552
but I miss the old town.

39
00:03:11,833 --> 00:03:14,549
Thought maybe I'd come back
and check out the old place,

40
00:03:14,830 --> 00:03:16,466
you know, see some
of my old friends.

41
00:03:16,747 --> 00:03:19,104
Hey, how's Kristen doing?

42
00:03:19,384 --> 00:03:21,501
Here it comes.

43
00:03:21,782 --> 00:03:23,459
She's good.

44
00:03:23,740 --> 00:03:25,736
Our kids are good too.
mean anything by it.

45
00:03:27,935 --> 00:03:29,493
I--you know,
I was just bein' polite.

46
00:03:29,814 --> 00:03:32,450
Look, we're not in high school
anymore, Dan.

47
00:03:33,530 --> 00:03:34,768
Look, I got to run.

48
00:03:35,049 --> 00:03:37,125
I've got a big moving van
with all my stuff in it,

49
00:03:37,406 --> 00:03:39,082
gonna take a look
at the old house.

50
00:03:39,363 --> 00:03:40,600
I'm sure I'll be seein'
you boys around though.

51
00:03:40,881 --> 00:03:42,159
Oh, yes, you will.

52
00:03:42,439 --> 00:03:44,077
All right.

53
00:03:46,036 --> 00:03:47,553
Moving van?

54
00:03:47,834 --> 00:03:50,470
Isn't exactly a home
for the holidays.

55
00:03:50,751 --> 00:03:54,586
Hey, you want me
to follow him?

56
00:04:00,820 --> 00:04:02,337
Pretty good, huh?

57
00:04:02,618 --> 00:04:03,975
Not bad.

58
00:04:04,256 --> 00:04:05,374
Not a winning time, but--

59
00:04:05,655 --> 00:04:07,692
Want me to time you?

60
00:04:08,013 --> 00:04:09,570
No, I don't want
to hold you up.

61
00:04:09,890 --> 00:04:11,208
I can wait.

62
00:04:11,488 --> 00:04:13,525
I'm just takin'
it easy today.

63
00:04:13,846 --> 00:04:15,124
Christmas Cup is coming up.

64
00:04:15,405 --> 00:04:16,842
You entering?
Of course.

65
00:04:17,123 --> 00:04:21,717
Me too.
Good luck.

66
00:04:29,789 --> 00:04:31,586
I'm gonna be the angel!

67
00:04:31,867 --> 00:04:33,464
You already are an angel.

68
00:04:33,745 --> 00:04:34,982
In the Christmas program,
Dad.

69
00:04:35,303 --> 00:04:36,501
That means I get lines.

70
00:04:36,782 --> 00:04:38,539
Wow, lines.

71
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:39,937
All the other kids
just have to sing,

72
00:04:40,258 --> 00:04:43,134
but I get to say stuff
too, and wear a costume.

73
00:04:43,415 --> 00:04:46,531
Oh, I am so glad
you're home.

74
00:04:47,889 --> 00:04:49,566
Can you help set the table?

75
00:04:49,887 --> 00:04:55,001
I have people
who do that for me.

76
00:04:55,282 --> 00:04:56,559
What happened?

77
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:57,998
What do you mean?

78
00:04:58,279 --> 00:05:00,076
You onlyjoke about your lack
of actual power

79
00:05:00,357 --> 00:05:02,034
when you've had
a run-in at work.

80
00:05:02,314 --> 00:05:03,751
Is that true?

81
00:05:05,790 --> 00:05:08,826
Hmm, well,
nothing happened.

82
00:05:10,385 --> 00:05:12,062
Okay.

83
00:05:16,699 --> 00:05:20,453
Mitch Bright
stopped by town today.

84
00:05:20,734 --> 00:05:22,412
High school Mitch Bright?

85
00:05:22,692 --> 00:05:23,770
Mm-hmm.

86
00:05:24,091 --> 00:05:25,728
Is he the rich guy?

87
00:05:27,607 --> 00:05:30,283
When I was waiting
for you at school,

88
00:05:30,564 --> 00:05:32,600
all the other teachers
were talking about it.

89
00:05:32,921 --> 00:05:35,557
Somebody saw him
in a big moving van.

90
00:05:35,878 --> 00:05:37,355
I thought you
were supposed to be

91
00:05:37,676 --> 00:05:38,994
your mother's
teacher assistant?

92
00:05:39,274 --> 00:05:40,592
She won't let me
grade the papers.

93
00:05:40,873 --> 00:05:41,990
Ooh.

94
00:05:42,271 --> 00:05:43,389
So he had
a big moving van?

95
00:05:43,710 --> 00:05:44,587
Mm-hmm.

96
00:05:44,868 --> 00:05:45,987
Hey, where's Cody?

97
00:05:46,267 --> 00:05:47,585
Cody, dinner's ready!

98
00:05:47,865 --> 00:05:49,942
He says he's home
for the holidays.

99
00:05:50,223 --> 00:05:52,739
Yeah, but his family
hasn't been here in years.

100
00:05:53,020 --> 00:05:55,256
Yeah, I know.

101
00:05:55,537 --> 00:05:58,612
Seems highly suspect.

102
00:05:58,893 --> 00:06:01,329
Well, you think we should
invite him for dinner?

103
00:06:01,610 --> 00:06:03,687
Oh, no, I don't think we can
feed him in the manner to which

104
00:06:04,008 --> 00:06:05,126
he has become accustomed.

105
00:06:05,407 --> 00:06:06,724
Oh, come on.

106
00:06:08,603 --> 00:06:09,641
Yes, you do.

107
00:06:09,962 --> 00:06:12,478
Cody!
Oh, hi honey, sorry.

108
00:06:12,798 --> 00:06:13,757
Okay.

109
00:06:14,037 --> 00:06:16,474
All right.

110
00:06:18,672 --> 00:06:20,029
Hey, what's wrong
with you?

111
00:06:20,310 --> 00:06:22,826
All the girls are reading
these vampire books.

112
00:06:23,746 --> 00:06:24,904
I don't get it.

113
00:06:25,185 --> 00:06:27,621
He wants the girls
to be in love with him instead.

114
00:06:27,902 --> 00:06:29,619
Okay, all right.

115
00:06:29,900 --> 00:06:31,178
Listen, your mom
read all those books.

116
00:06:31,499 --> 00:06:32,776
I know exactly how you feel.

117
00:06:33,057 --> 00:06:36,572
Mmm, can we please find
something to thank God for?

118
00:06:36,852 --> 00:06:38,969
Yes.
I get to be the angel.

119
00:06:39,290 --> 00:06:41,486
It's gonna be the best
Christmas ever.

120
00:06:58,229 --> 00:07:00,626
That was fast.

121
00:07:00,907 --> 00:07:02,385
Thanks for lettin' me drive.

122
00:07:02,706 --> 00:07:04,062
Yeah.

123
00:07:04,343 --> 00:07:06,180
That's the last time.

124
00:07:19,846 --> 00:07:22,243
So who's that guy you were
talking about last night?

125
00:07:22,524 --> 00:07:23,482
Mitch Bright.

126
00:07:23,763 --> 00:07:26,677
Just a guy
from back in the day.

127
00:07:28,037 --> 00:07:30,833
We didn't get along
too well unfortunately.

128
00:07:31,114 --> 00:07:34,149
You had a high school rival?

129
00:07:34,430 --> 00:07:35,469
Yeah, why?

130
00:07:35,789 --> 00:07:38,226
What's so unusual
about that?

131
00:07:38,507 --> 00:07:41,382
Just seems like
everybody likes you.

132
00:07:41,703 --> 00:07:44,899
You need to go to some
city council meetings.

133
00:07:46,298 --> 00:07:48,016
So what did you
guys compete over?

134
00:07:48,336 --> 00:07:50,372
Oh, everything.

135
00:07:50,652 --> 00:07:55,366
Football, basketball, skiing,
running, class offices,

136
00:07:55,647 --> 00:07:59,523
parking spaces...mom.

137
00:07:59,804 --> 00:08:01,481
Mom?

138
00:08:01,761 --> 00:08:03,199
I won that one.

139
00:08:03,479 --> 00:08:04,438
Really?

140
00:08:04,719 --> 00:08:10,431
Your mom was
the girl in high school.

141
00:08:10,712 --> 00:08:13,587
Still is.

142
00:08:15,226 --> 00:08:17,903
Now you're lucky if you made
it this far without a rival,

143
00:08:18,183 --> 00:08:20,980
without someone to push you
and try to beat you

144
00:08:21,261 --> 00:08:23,057
at what you're good at.

145
00:08:23,338 --> 00:08:25,255
I didn't say that.

146
00:08:25,576 --> 00:08:26,773
Really?

147
00:08:28,213 --> 00:08:30,930
Somebody's givin' you trouble?

148
00:08:31,249 --> 00:08:35,484
My situation's a lot
different than yours.

149
00:08:35,765 --> 00:08:37,602
Yours seems a lot easier.

150
00:08:37,882 --> 00:08:39,240
Of course.

151
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:41,517
Of course yours is worse.

152
00:08:42,598 --> 00:08:45,553
How is yours worse?

153
00:08:45,834 --> 00:08:48,190
Mine's a girl.

154
00:08:48,471 --> 00:08:50,308
Okay.

155
00:08:53,626 --> 00:08:55,143
Morning.

156
00:08:55,424 --> 00:08:57,102
Good mornin'.

157
00:08:57,381 --> 00:08:59,937
Can I get a cafe Americano
with soy, please?

158
00:09:00,218 --> 00:09:01,776
Sure.

159
00:09:02,057 --> 00:09:05,252
Hey, now Josie,
how's business?

160
00:09:05,572 --> 00:09:07,249
I can't complain.

161
00:09:07,570 --> 00:09:08,649
Customers are loyal.

162
00:09:08,929 --> 00:09:11,446
What do you think it
would take to make it better?

163
00:09:11,726 --> 00:09:13,843
More customers, I guess.

164
00:09:14,123 --> 00:09:15,441
Exactly.

165
00:09:15,722 --> 00:09:17,919
You know, I have some ideas
on how I think

166
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:19,397
I can make that happen.

167
00:09:19,678 --> 00:09:21,035
You interested?

168
00:09:21,315 --> 00:09:22,433
Sure.

169
00:09:22,714 --> 00:09:23,591
Good.

170
00:09:28,627 --> 00:09:33,063
Man, Christmas
is an awesome time of year,

171
00:09:33,342 --> 00:09:34,421
am I right?

172
00:09:34,742 --> 00:09:36,259
Hey, Santa.

173
00:09:36,539 --> 00:09:37,858
No, really.
I mean, think about it,

174
00:09:38,138 --> 00:09:39,855
this is
the only time of year

175
00:09:40,136 --> 00:09:43,531
the entire world has this like
shared experience of peace

176
00:09:43,812 --> 00:09:48,485
and hope for the future and
strangers are lovin' each other.

177
00:09:48,766 --> 00:09:51,842
And there's that somethin'
in the air, man, it's something.

178
00:09:59,156 --> 00:10:00,713
What is wrong with you?

179
00:10:01,033 --> 00:10:02,271
It's been a great week, man.

180
00:10:02,552 --> 00:10:03,430
Are you kiddin' me?

181
00:10:03,711 --> 00:10:07,345
We had two ice fishermen
and the snow machine tool.

182
00:10:07,625 --> 00:10:14,337
Kristen invited Mitch to our
Christmas party Sunday night.

183
00:10:14,658 --> 00:10:17,454
She said it was
the Christian thing to do.

184
00:10:17,775 --> 00:10:20,172
Man, why does Kristen
always have to be right?

185
00:10:20,453 --> 00:10:21,650
Yeah.

186
00:10:23,449 --> 00:10:26,245
I know he's got an angle.

187
00:10:26,566 --> 00:10:31,959
Now why would he come back
here after so many years?

188
00:10:32,719 --> 00:10:35,674
What's he after?

189
00:10:35,955 --> 00:10:37,433
I don't know.

190
00:10:37,713 --> 00:10:40,150
Maybe he's just weary
of his city life

191
00:10:40,430 --> 00:10:43,506
and he wants to return
to the simple town of his youth.

192
00:10:43,787 --> 00:10:46,544
Or he's still mad at ya
after all the times you beat him

193
00:10:46,864 --> 00:10:48,342
in high school.

194
00:10:48,622 --> 00:10:50,579
And so after festering
for 20 years,

195
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:53,216
he's returned
to exact his revenge.

196
00:10:56,414 --> 00:10:57,931
Yeah, you know, could
you back to singing?

197
00:10:58,211 --> 00:11:00,408
Because you're
a lot less annoying.

198
00:11:00,729 --> 00:11:03,205
Thanks for the help.

199
00:11:07,762 --> 00:11:10,478
Well, it's getting late.

200
00:11:10,759 --> 00:11:14,354
You know I wasn't arguing
about your policies.

201
00:11:14,634 --> 00:11:17,030
It's--well, it's
more your approach.

202
00:11:17,351 --> 00:11:18,948
I don't know
what you mean.

203
00:11:19,269 --> 00:11:20,986
I think the mistake that
you're making is assuming

204
00:11:21,266 --> 00:11:22,864
that you're every man.

205
00:11:23,184 --> 00:11:26,860
I find your ideals to be wildly
conservative compared

206
00:11:27,141 --> 00:11:29,138
to the rest of the country.

207
00:11:29,418 --> 00:11:31,295
This is comin' from the guy
that went to Berkeley

208
00:11:31,576 --> 00:11:33,053
and lived in San Francisco
for 1 0 years,

209
00:11:33,334 --> 00:11:37,568
'cause when I think every man,
I think San Francisco.

210
00:11:39,447 --> 00:11:42,362
When's the last time
you left Alaska?

211
00:11:42,683 --> 00:11:43,762
I don't know, Mitch.

212
00:11:44,042 --> 00:11:45,799
I've been so busy buildin'
bomb shelters

213
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:48,397
and publishing
conspiracy papers

214
00:11:48,678 --> 00:11:50,435
that I haven't had time
to get out.

215
00:11:50,715 --> 00:11:53,072
Look, just 'cause we're
the 49th state doesn't make us

216
00:11:53,393 --> 00:11:54,550
a third world.

217
00:11:54,831 --> 00:11:57,227
Look, there is a surprising
amount of hocus-pocus here.

218
00:11:57,508 --> 00:12:00,265
Oh, you mean--what,
Native religion?

219
00:12:00,545 --> 00:12:01,901
No, I mean Christianity.

220
00:12:02,222 --> 00:12:04,099
Well, it seems I recall you
competing with Dan

221
00:12:04,380 --> 00:12:06,577
for president of the youth group
back in the day.

222
00:12:06,897 --> 00:12:08,694
Well, there isn't much I
wouldn't compete with Dan about,

223
00:12:10,414 --> 00:12:12,731
So, that was an act?

224
00:12:13,012 --> 00:12:14,169
No, not an act.

225
00:12:14,450 --> 00:12:17,406
Look, ifyou had an opportunity
to travel the world as I have,

226
00:12:17,727 --> 00:12:19,604
you would know that
American culture is not limited

227
00:12:19,884 --> 00:12:22,401
to this small town bubble
that you live in.

228
00:12:22,721 --> 00:12:28,553
America is vast and diverse
and loving, peaceful, tolerant.

229
00:12:28,834 --> 00:12:31,750
Yeah, no, I'm just--
I'm trying to understand

230
00:12:32,031 --> 00:12:34,388
what you're implying.

231
00:12:34,667 --> 00:12:36,745
I would be willing to wager
that a majority of the people

232
00:12:37,025 --> 00:12:40,581
in this town find your
religious piety annoying.

233
00:12:40,862 --> 00:12:41,859
Annoying?

234
00:12:42,180 --> 00:12:43,298
Yes.

235
00:12:43,579 --> 00:12:45,416
And they reelect me because?

236
00:12:45,697 --> 00:12:47,692
Well, you ran unopposed
in the last two elections, Dan.

237
00:12:48,013 --> 00:12:50,490
Because he's doing
such a good job.

238
00:12:50,811 --> 00:12:51,928
Yes.

239
00:12:52,209 --> 00:12:55,964
I'm sure he is
in a very small town way.

240
00:12:56,244 --> 00:12:58,362
I don't agree
with you, Mitch.

241
00:12:58,682 --> 00:13:00,400
Just because God's out ofvogue
in the big city doesn't mean

242
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:03,316
we throw him away like last
summer's fashion magazine.

243
00:13:03,637 --> 00:13:04,675
Maybe you wouldn't.

244
00:13:04,956 --> 00:13:06,553
Maybe a lot of your
close friends

245
00:13:06,834 --> 00:13:08,391
that were here tonight wouldn't.

246
00:13:08,672 --> 00:13:13,505
But I guess there's
no way to prove it, is there?

247
00:13:13,785 --> 00:13:18,660
You know, maybe I would
make a good mayor someday.

248
00:13:18,940 --> 00:13:20,138
You might.

249
00:13:20,418 --> 00:13:21,497
Yeah, I kinda like that.

250
00:13:21,778 --> 00:13:24,813
Mayor Mitch Bright.
Has a ring to it.

251
00:13:25,134 --> 00:13:26,252
Good night!

252
00:13:26,533 --> 00:13:28,489
Good night.

253
00:13:34,563 --> 00:13:35,801
Hey!

254
00:13:36,082 --> 00:13:37,799
Hey, sweetie.

255
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:39,197
Can I come in?

256
00:13:39,518 --> 00:13:40,436
Yeah!

257
00:13:40,757 --> 00:13:42,714
I didn't know
if you're closed or...

258
00:13:42,995 --> 00:13:44,432
The second time in today.

259
00:13:44,713 --> 00:13:46,549
I'm unforgettable.

260
00:13:47,390 --> 00:13:48,428
Coffee, black?

261
00:13:48,708 --> 00:13:49,826
Yup.

262
00:13:50,107 --> 00:13:51,384
Unless you got another color.

263
00:13:51,665 --> 00:13:52,984
No, that's it.

264
00:13:53,303 --> 00:13:54,821
