three options to consider.

1037
00:53:55,522 --> 00:53:59,037
I mean, you could add to this
as a holiday display and include

1038
00:53:59,316 --> 00:54:01,713
elements of a nonreligious
nature or elements

1039
00:54:02,034 --> 00:54:04,590
that are of other faiths.

1040
00:54:04,911 --> 00:54:08,227
Or the city can donate
or sell them,

1041
00:54:08,508 --> 00:54:12,103
the statues and the platform,
to a private individual

1042
00:54:12,383 --> 00:54:14,540
who can display them
in another place,

1043
00:54:14,821 --> 00:54:17,058
either on private property

1044
00:54:17,378 --> 00:54:19,455
or with permission
in a public setting

1045
00:54:19,735 --> 00:54:21,412
where there is
equal opportunity for others

1046
00:54:21,693 --> 00:54:23,570
to put up their own
holiday displays.

1047
00:54:23,850 --> 00:54:25,289
And the third?

1048
00:54:25,568 --> 00:54:27,007
Don't display them at all.

1049
00:54:27,327 --> 00:54:30,204
But if you ask me,
that would be a shame.

1050
00:54:30,483 --> 00:54:32,361
With all due respect,
your Honor,

1051
00:54:32,642 --> 00:54:34,599
all three of those are ruining
our town's traditions

1052
00:54:34,880 --> 00:54:36,757
that we've had over 50 years.

1053
00:54:37,077 --> 00:54:40,113
Or you could look at it
as creating a new tradition.

1054
00:54:40,393 --> 00:54:44,508
I mean, moving the Christ child
to another place of honor

1055
00:54:49,823 --> 00:54:53,418
Perhaps you are more
concerned about yours.

1056
00:54:53,739 --> 00:54:55,856
And this is
my advice on the case,

1057
00:54:56,137 --> 00:54:58,533
if you want to push
for an official ruling,
will have to come down.

1058
00:55:00,892 --> 00:55:03,688
Otherwise, let me know what
you choose to do, okay?

1059
00:55:03,968 --> 00:55:05,206
Thank you, your Honor.

1060
00:55:05,486 --> 00:55:06,483
Yes, thank you.

1061
00:55:06,764 --> 00:55:07,883
Thank you, your Honor.

1062
00:55:08,203 --> 00:55:09,680
Merry Christmas.

1063
00:55:11,479 --> 00:55:13,396
Merry Christmas.

1064
00:55:14,556 --> 00:55:16,473
Big cruise ships
comin' up through here,

1065
00:55:16,754 --> 00:55:18,471
people tramplin' all over.

1066
00:55:18,752 --> 00:55:19,950
You know,
he says it's gonna bring

1067
00:55:20,231 --> 00:55:21,868
a bunch of money into town.

1068
00:55:22,149 --> 00:55:24,146
'Cause Alaska cruises,
you know, they got a lot

1069
00:55:24,426 --> 00:55:26,463
of retired people, you know,
old people, you know,

1070
00:55:26,784 --> 00:55:31,337
goin' on those shoestring budget
transportation tours together.

1071
00:55:31,658 --> 00:55:34,374
Bunch of old, widowed ladies.

1072
00:55:36,493 --> 00:55:39,529
Old, widowed ladies?

1073
00:55:40,449 --> 00:55:42,285
You got another one of those?

1074
00:55:51,636 --> 00:55:53,114
Coach.

1075
00:55:53,395 --> 00:55:54,392
Mayor.

1076
00:55:54,673 --> 00:55:56,750
Wow, nice button.

1077
00:55:57,070 --> 00:55:58,549
He's gonna bring
the cruise line order

1078
00:55:58,868 --> 00:56:00,187
to the race on Saturday.

1079
00:56:00,467 --> 00:56:01,345
Isn't that great?

1080
00:56:01,626 --> 00:56:03,742
Yeah, that's great.

1081
00:56:04,023 --> 00:56:06,100
See you inside, Coach.

1082
00:56:06,381 --> 00:56:09,057
You know, I can help you
tear this thing down.

1083
00:56:10,736 --> 00:56:12,574
I don't believe you would
actually help me

1084
00:56:12,855 --> 00:56:14,651
even if I planned
on takin' it down.

1085
00:56:14,931 --> 00:56:16,888
Oh, I could hire somebody.

1086
00:56:17,169 --> 00:56:18,646
It's not goin' anywhere.

1087
00:56:18,927 --> 00:56:20,844
Now you heard what
the judge said, Dan.

1088
00:56:21,125 --> 00:56:25,759
There's nothin' religious
about a bunch of planks of wood.

1089
00:56:26,040 --> 00:56:27,517
Look, ifyou want
to let it sit here empty,

1090
00:56:27,798 --> 00:56:29,156
that's fine with me.

1091
00:56:29,437 --> 00:56:31,114
I told you that you
were in the minority,

1092
00:56:31,394 --> 00:56:32,592
but you wouldn't listen.

1093
00:56:32,872 --> 00:56:35,509
Guess we'll find out come
spring election, huh?

1094
00:57:12,749 --> 00:57:14,267
I got cocoa.

1095
00:57:14,548 --> 00:57:15,945
Mom, look
at how long mine is.

1096
00:57:16,226 --> 00:57:18,223
No, no, no, no no!

1097
00:57:18,504 --> 00:57:22,338
You always get the railroads,
and I want to be the tycoon.

1098
00:57:22,619 --> 00:57:27,092
Why don't you send some
more marshmallows our way, huh?

1099
00:57:28,213 --> 00:57:31,529
Danny boy,
wife's talkin' to ya.

1100
00:57:32,968 --> 00:57:35,284
He's still mad
'cause he lost.

1101
00:57:35,605 --> 00:57:37,242
Hey, hey, let's
do a midnight run.

1102
00:57:37,563 --> 00:57:39,999
Me, you, and Cody,
we'll take the nativity,

1103
00:57:40,320 --> 00:57:41,398
we'll stick it in the church.

1104
00:57:41,678 --> 00:57:43,915
No, no, no, let's
take it to the park.

1105
00:57:44,236 --> 00:57:45,434
That'd make you happy.

1106
00:57:45,714 --> 00:57:47,431
The Grinch ruined Christmas.

1107
00:57:47,712 --> 00:57:49,149
It doesn't make you mad?

1108
00:57:49,430 --> 00:57:51,306
He didn't ruin my Christmas.

1109
00:57:51,587 --> 00:57:53,304
Mine's okay.

1110
00:57:53,585 --> 00:57:55,263
I mean,
I'd be a little grinchy too

1111
00:57:55,544 --> 00:57:56,821
if all I had in my house

1112
00:57:57,142 --> 00:57:59,139
was a little couch
and a suitcase.

1113
00:57:59,420 --> 00:58:01,057
What do you mean?

1114
00:58:01,337 --> 00:58:02,336
Yeah.

1115
00:58:02,617 --> 00:58:06,491
We're still talking
about Mitch Bright, right?
you talking about?

1116
00:58:08,609 --> 00:58:10,126
Remember when we
delivered the cookies?

1117
00:58:10,407 --> 00:58:11,445
Well, when I looked
in the window,

1118
00:58:11,766 --> 00:58:14,362
all I saw was a little couch
and a suitcase.

1119
00:58:14,683 --> 00:58:18,878
Wait a minute,
in that whole big house?

1120
00:58:19,158 --> 00:58:23,113
What about his
grandmother's antiques?

1121
00:58:23,434 --> 00:58:25,311
And the moving van?

1122
00:58:25,591 --> 00:58:26,709
Wait a minute.

1123
00:58:26,990 --> 00:58:30,466
Are you tellin' me that the van
was taking antiques

1124
00:58:30,746 --> 00:58:32,382
away from his house?

1125
00:58:32,663 --> 00:58:34,780
Hang on, hang on,
let me try to figure this out.

1126
00:58:35,101 --> 00:58:36,738
I knew somethin' was wrong.

1127
00:58:37,058 --> 00:58:41,133
Okay, so Mitch Bright
comes to town,

1128
00:58:41,414 --> 00:58:43,570
he sells or loses
everything he has.

1129
00:58:43,891 --> 00:58:47,207
He puts on this big show about
how rich, how successful he is,

1130
00:58:47,488 --> 00:58:48,605
how he's gonna save the town.

1131
00:58:48,886 --> 00:58:50,164
He's gonna run for mayor.

1132
00:58:50,445 --> 00:58:53,920
He puts the whole town
on edge over Christmas.

1133
00:58:54,200 --> 00:58:56,277
Now that really makes sense.

1134
00:58:56,598 --> 00:59:00,752
I think this makes for a very
interesting story, don't you?

1135
00:59:01,033 --> 00:59:02,351
But what is it?

1136
00:59:02,631 --> 00:59:04,749
Well maybe it's
none of our business.

1137
00:59:05,028 --> 00:59:06,267
Who wants more popcorn?

1138
00:59:06,547 --> 00:59:07,425
Me!

1139
00:59:07,706 --> 00:59:08,944
Cody ate all mine.

1140
00:59:09,265 --> 00:59:10,622
You know what this
means, don't you?

1141
00:59:10,903 --> 00:59:12,220
Road trip.

1142
00:59:12,501 --> 00:59:13,379
Oh, I know that look.

1143
00:59:13,660 --> 00:59:16,376
You Reed brothers
are scheming again.

1144
00:59:16,657 --> 00:59:17,854
You know what, honey?

1145
00:59:18,134 --> 00:59:19,611
Greg and I are gonna pay
a little visit

1146
00:59:19,932 --> 00:59:21,290
to Mitch Bright's law firm.

1147
00:59:21,570 --> 00:59:22,768
I'm gonna call Harland.

1148
00:59:23,049 --> 00:59:24,167
I'll have him get
the plane ready.

1149
00:59:24,447 --> 00:59:25,766
All right.

1150
00:59:26,046 --> 00:59:29,401
Your roll, Donald Trump.

1151
00:59:38,833 --> 00:59:42,148
Now, I mean, would it kill
you to let me be left seat once?

1152
00:59:42,468 --> 00:59:44,505
It might.
and we show up to this office,

1153
00:59:47,942 --> 00:59:49,220
you let me do the talking.

1154
00:59:49,501 --> 00:59:50,898
You sure this is a good idea?

1155
00:59:51,219 --> 00:59:52,736
'Cause I'm usually
game for anything.

1156
00:59:53,057 --> 00:59:54,175
I know.

1157
00:59:54,456 --> 00:59:56,733
I hope so.

1158
00:59:57,054 --> 00:59:59,490
I gotta take a wiz.

1159
01:00:03,605 --> 01:00:05,203
You're friends
of Mitch Bright?

1160
01:00:05,483 --> 01:00:07,360
We went to high school
with him.

1161
01:00:07,681 --> 01:00:08,799
We're in town.

1162
01:00:09,080 --> 01:00:10,357
Thought we'd
stop by and say hey.

1163
01:00:10,678 --> 01:00:11,835
Well, sorry
to keep you waiting.

1164
01:00:12,116 --> 01:00:13,834
He doesn't work
here anymore.

1165
01:00:14,114 --> 01:00:15,872
Oh.

1166
01:00:16,153 --> 01:00:19,108
Well, maybe you could tell us
what firm he went to or give us

1167
01:00:19,429 --> 01:00:20,627
an address where we
could look him up?

1168
01:00:20,908 --> 01:00:23,743
No.

1169
01:00:25,503 --> 01:00:29,257
What, is it cloak and dagger
or is he big trouble?

1170
01:00:29,538 --> 01:00:31,654
No, sorry, the firm's
just protective.

1171
01:00:34,053 --> 01:00:37,249
Mitch was never
anything but nice to me.

1172
01:00:37,530 --> 01:00:39,327
He gave me a shot
at a few cases a while back

1173
01:00:39,607 --> 01:00:42,444
and he helped me
get on good track here.

1174
01:00:43,843 --> 01:00:45,920
And all I know is is that he
ended up investing in something

1175
01:00:46,200 --> 01:00:49,475
he shouldn't have.

1176
01:00:49,796 --> 01:00:52,871
It went south.

1177
01:00:54,870 --> 01:00:59,744
He ended up losing everything,
including his job here.

1178
01:01:01,823 --> 01:01:04,259
Then, of course, nobody
ever talks about it.

1179
01:01:04,540 --> 01:01:06,058
I don't know where he went

1180
01:01:06,379 --> 01:01:08,136
or if he has any family
or friends to go to.

1181
01:01:08,417 --> 01:01:13,610
Well, his family's gone,
but he has--you know,

1182
01:01:13,889 --> 01:01:15,368
he has friends.

1183
01:01:15,648 --> 01:01:17,405
Like you guys?

1184
01:01:17,686 --> 01:01:18,843
Yeah.

1185
01:01:19,124 --> 01:01:21,001
Yeah, right.

1186
01:01:21,282 --> 01:01:25,317
When you see him,
you give him this.

1187
01:01:25,598 --> 01:01:29,033
Just tell him it's from an old
friend or do it anonymously.

1188
01:01:29,314 --> 01:01:31,031
I don't think that we could--

1189
01:01:31,312 --> 01:01:33,508
No, please.
to take it, but he needs it.

1190
01:01:37,744 --> 01:01:40,580
He really helped me
out a lot back then.

1191
01:01:40,861 --> 01:01:44,217
I just want to help him.

1192
01:01:45,256 --> 01:01:48,292
Well, that's all I know,
so I better get back to work.

1193
01:01:48,573 --> 01:01:49,691
Good luck to both of you.

1194
01:01:49,971 --> 01:01:51,849
Yeah, thanks for--

1195
01:01:52,169 --> 01:01:54,087
Good luck
and Merry Christmas.

1196
01:01:54,367 --> 01:01:57,402
Merry Christmas to you.

1197
01:02:00,840 --> 01:02:05,274
So he's ruined, he comes
back to town hiding the fact.

1198
01:02:05,555 --> 01:02:07,831
What do you think
he's trying to do?

1199
01:02:08,112 --> 01:02:09,869
Get a life back.

1200
01:02:10,150 --> 01:02:12,027
Not a very good strategy
to run for mayor

1201
01:02:12,308 --> 01:02:13,905
while lying to everybody.

1202
01:02:14,186 --> 01:02:15,544
Yeah.

1203
01:02:15,824 --> 01:02:18,500
You know, I think this
whole cruise line thing

1204
01:02:18,781 --> 01:02:21,496
is just to get back in the game.

1205
01:02:21,777 --> 01:02:26,491
Maybe people will forgive him
when they find out the truth.

1206
01:02:27,491 --> 01:02:29,768
Or we could run him
out of here on a rail.

1207
01:02:30,088 --> 01:02:32,844
Yeah, that'd show him
the real spirit of Christmas.

1208
01:02:33,165 --> 01:02:34,323
It'd sure feel good.

1209
01:02:34,604 --> 01:02:36,441
Yeah.

1210
01:02:37,960 --> 01:02:39,238
Hey, Dad.

1211
01:02:39,519 --> 01:02:40,516
Hey, pal.
What's up?

1212
01:02:40,837 --> 01:02:42,354
Can you help me
with these?

1213
01:02:42,635 --> 01:02:43,633
Sure.

1214
01:02:43,953 --> 01:02:46,270
Sure.
See you guys.

1215
01:02:46,551 --> 01:02:47,468
See you.

1216
01:02:47,789 --> 01:02:50,385
Ah, grab this
thing, will you?

1217
01:02:51,944 --> 01:02:53,343
What's up, man?

1218
01:02:53,663 --> 01:02:56,300
You know that girl
I was telling you about?

1219
01:02:56,620 --> 01:02:59,136
Uh, not sure.

1220
01:03:00,456 --> 01:03:02,413
You know, she's
always trying to beat me.

1221
01:03:02,694 --> 01:03:03,811
We talked about it.

1222
01:03:04,092 --> 01:03:05,250
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

1223
01:03:05,531 --> 01:03:06,847
What happened?

1224
01:03:07,168 --> 01:03:10,843
Well, see, we were racing.

1225
01:03:11,164 --> 01:03:12,282
Yeah.

1226
01:03:12,563 --> 01:03:16,877
She was winning,
but then she fell and hurt.

1227
01:03:17,158 --> 01:03:19,674
I thought it was my fault.

1228
01:03:19,995 --> 01:03:22,472
That's why I wasn't
going to enter the Cup.

1229
01:03:24,351 --> 01:03:27,307
She bribed me to race.

1230
01:03:27,627 --> 01:03:30,222
Does this make
any sense to you?

1231
01:03:30,543 --> 01:03:31,381
Not really.

1232
01:03:31,702 --> 01:03:32,819
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

1233
01:03:33,100 --> 01:03:34,219
I forgot something.

1234
01:03:34,538 --> 01:03:37,495
So what did you do
when she hurt herself?

1235
01:03:37,775 --> 01:03:40,052
I helped her back, of course.

1236
01:03:40,373 --> 01:03:42,290
I mean, I'm not a jerk.

1237
01:03:42,570 --> 01:03:44,247
Aw, you helped her all
the way back to school.

1238
01:03:44,528 --> 01:03:46,446
Oh, that was nice.

1239
01:03:46,726 --> 01:03:49,722
I'm sure she really
appreciated that.

1240
01:03:50,043 --> 01:03:52,239
She usually pretty fast?

1241
01:03:52,519 --> 01:03:53,956
Yeah, she's good.

1242
01:03:54,237 --> 01:03:55,436
Faster than you.

1243
01:03:55,716 --> 01:03:56,994
At least that day.

1244
01:03:57,274 --> 01:03:58,353
Yeah.

1245
01:03:58,633 --> 01:04:00,151
Careful, that's hot.

1246
01:04:00,432 --> 01:04:03,866
How are you at losing?

1247
01:04:04,147 --> 01:04:06,304
I try to be a good sport,
you know,

1248
01:04:06,625 --> 01:04:09,341
but it makes me mad
when I lose.

1249
01:04:12,339 --> 01:04:15,293
I wonder where
he got that from.

1250
01:04:15,614 --> 01:04:16,573
Seems like somebody's
listening in

1251
01:04:16,853 --> 01:04:18,450
on our conversation.

1252
01:04:18,731 --> 01:04:21,887
You guys are
so slow sometimes.

1253
01:04:23,446 --> 01:04:25,243
We do things
at our own speed.

1254
01:04:25,524 --> 01:04:28,201
It's called man time.

1255
01:04:28,481 --> 01:04:30,878
I'm getting to it.

1256
01:04:31,199 --> 01:04:35,713
Look, I don't think it's
the race she's trying to win.

1257
01:04:37,471 --> 01:04:39,348
I think it's you.

1258
01:04:39,629 --> 01:04:42,465
She's always bothering me.

1259
01:04:44,504 --> 01:04:48,658
Look, you have to get
past the competition.

1260
01:04:48,939 --> 01:04:50,257
You have to see the person.

1261
01:04:50,578 --> 01:04:51,735
She's just a young girl.

1262
01:04:52,016 --> 01:04:53,773
She got all this stuff
going on inside of her.

1263
01:04:54,054 --> 01:04:57,849
She doesn't know how
to express it, right?

1264
01:04:59,848 --> 01:05:02,803
Is that what you're doing?

1265
01:05:03,083 --> 01:05:05,201
Seeing the person there?

1266
01:05:05,481 --> 01:05:07,717
What do you mean?

1267
01:05:07,998 --> 01:05:11,314
With Mitch.

1268
01:05:11,595 --> 01:05:13,072
You've been doing all this
investigating, you know,

1269
01:05:13,353 --> 01:05:19,306
so I was just wondering if
you had him figured out too.

1270
01:05:19,586 --> 01:05:22,422
I don't know.

1271
01:05:22,743 --> 01:05:28,576
Look, you race tomorrow.

1272
01:05:28,856 --> 01:05:30,174
Do the best you can.

1273
01:05:30,454 --> 01:05:33,091
Win or lose, you have
worked so hard for this.

1274
01:05:33,372 --> 01:05:38,206
You just go out there
and give it everything you have.

1275
01:05:38,526 --> 01:05:40,163
All right?
You owe that to yourself.

1276
01:05:40,484 --> 01:05:43,281
Yes, sir.

1277
01:05:43,560 --> 01:05:48,274
Is she--is she cute?

1278
01:05:48,554 --> 01:05:50,032
Yeah.

1279
01:05:50,313 --> 01:05:53,189
That's my boy.

1280
01:06:06,776 --> 01:06:08,852
Hey, Dan, I haven't seen
Mitch and his big guest yet,

1281
01:06:09,133 --> 01:06:10,210
have you?

1282
01:06:10,531 --> 01:06:11,649
No.

1283
01:06:11,930 --> 01:06:13,887
He's coming, isn't he?
Right?

1284
01:06:14,168 --> 01:06:15,925
Mitch promised he would.

1285
01:06:16,205 --> 01:06:17,722
I guess we'll see.

1286
01:06:18,003 --> 01:06:22,078
Sure hope he makes it 'cause
you remember, like you said,

1287
01:06:22,399 --> 01:06:25,275
be good for my business.

1288
01:06:29,871 --> 01:06:31,667
Loser takes the winner
for moose burgers.

1289
01:06:31,988 --> 01:06:34,264
